{"type":"assistant.message","data":{"messageId":"562d8898-702c-4edd-9e31-16d5cdabbdb5","content":"\n\nHere are the most common options depending on your stack:\n\n**ASP.NET Core (`dotnet new`)**\n- `webapi` — minimal API or controller-based\n- Auth options: `--auth` flag with values:\n  - `None` (default)\n  - `Individual` — local Identity-based auth\n  - `IndividualB2C` — Azure AD B2C\n  - `SingleOrg` — Azure AD single-tenant\n  - `MultiOrg` — Azure AD multi-tenant\n  - `Windows` — Windows/Negotiate auth\n\n**Node.js** — Express/Fastify + Passport.js, or NestJS with `@nestjs/passport`\n\n**Python** — FastAPI with OAuth2/JWT, or Django REST Framework with `djangorestframework-simplejwt`\n\nFor .NET specifically:\n```bash\ndotnet new webapi --auth Individual -o MyApi\n```\n\nWant me to scaffold a project with a specific stack and auth type?","toolRequests":[],"interactionId":"7eaa58ca-823f-4e56-92e7-686fc428c5ea","reasoningOpaque":"","reasoningText":"The user is asking a general knowledge question about web API project templates and authentication options. This doesn't require any tool calls - I can answer from my knowledge of common web frameworks.\n\nLet me provide a concise answer covering the most common options.","outputTokens":295},"id":"cc61ecf4-935d-44fe-aaa0-b92c9202c0e2","timestamp":"2026-04-04T00:43:52.919Z","parentId":"b39db7d3-92f9-4f49-aeb0-f952b0b42a0e"}
